title: India launches two patrol vessels
description: Two additional water-jet propelled Inshore Patrol Vessels (IPV) of Indian Coast Guard (ICG) were launched at newly acquired and refurbished Rajabagan dockyard in Calcutta, India, on Aug. 6, 2012.
cleanContent:
Two additional water-jet propelled Inshore Patrol Vessels (IPV) of Indian Coast Guard (ICG) are launched at newly acquired and refurbished Rajabagan dockyard in Calcutta, India, on Aug. 6, 2012.(Xinhua/Tumpa Mondal)

One of two additional water-jet propelled Inshore Patrol Vessels (IPV) of Indian Coast Guard (ICG) is launched at newly acquired and refurbished Rajabagan dockyard in Calcutta, India, on Aug. 6, 2012.(Xinhua/Tumpa Mondal)

Two additional water-jet propelled Inshore Patrol Vessels (IPV) of Indian Coast Guard (ICG) were launched at newly acquired and refurbished Rajabagan dockyard in Calcutta, India, on Aug. 6, 2012. | |
